<br />
If the devs are tuning around group content (as stated above), arguments that involve &quot;screwing group content&quot; is unlikely to have any ground to stand on, imho. Rather, we should demonstrate to the devs, that a long re-use disc (or a short re-use disc with reduced effect) would not seriously overpowered us in a grouping situation, but give us the edge we lack in a burst burn raid situation. <br />
<br />
And the whole &quot;Gimme more mana, gimme free ooc all the time&quot;, sounds to me as a &quot;I want to be able to chain instants and EI throughout a fight, allow me this and I might be satisfied&quot;, which is going in a completely different direction  to what the devs have -insisted- on taking us.<br />
<br />
I'm dubious to the whole thing though until I get a chance to parse more fights (only done two of any use, non of which were really burst burn fights). With the fights I've parsed so far, it seems as if I'm pretty well-balanced with my melee peers atm, and shifting that in either direction wouldn't be fair (and would threatend to overpower solo abilities, I suspect). So perhaps it is really just the high-end that requires tuning at this point.</div>
